translated: Larsson, Axel (Acke) Julius, district physician, Gothenburg, b. 4/6/02 in Stockholm to engineer Axel L. and Klara Persson. Married on 31st (month not specified) to Greta Häggblad. Children: Håkan Julius b. 35, Eva Margareta b. 38, Gun Marianne b. 43. Graduated from Södertälje in 1921, received a Bachelor of Medicine in 1925 and a Medical License in 1931 from the Karolinska Institute. Worked as an assistant at the State Bacteriology Laboratory from 1929-1930, then as a physician at St. Gertrud's Hospital from 1931. Served as acting chief medical officer in the districts of Broby, Stugun, and Föllinge in 1931 and 1934, acting assistant physician at Are Mountain Sanatorium from 1931-1932, temporary and regular assistant physician at the County Sanatorium in Uttran in 1933, assistant physician at Skellefteå Hospital Medical Department in 1934, second assistant physician at the County Sanatorium in Uttran from 1934-1935, and thereafter as first assistant physician at the Vänersborg Hospital Medical Department from 1935-1938. Became an assistant medical officer at Löwenström Hospital in 1938, acting chief medical officer in the districts of Robertsfors, Umeå, and others from 1939-1940. Currently employed as a district physician in Gothenburg and first flight doctor at the (abbreviated) Flying Corps.
